# Package Manager: pnpm Only

All projects use **pnpm v10**. Never use npm or yarn for any operation.

## Rules

- Use `pnpm add` to install packages, never `npm install` or `npm i`
- Use `pnpm add -g` for global installs, never `npm install -g`
- Use `pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm start` to run scripts
- Use `pnpm remove` to uninstall packages
- Never run `npm`, `npx`, or `yarn` commands
- When a package blocks install due to `minimumReleaseAge`, add it to `minimumReleaseAgeExclude` in `pnpm-workspace.yaml` temporarily
- When a package needs build scripts, add it to `onlyBuiltDependencies` in `pnpm-workspace.yaml`
- Use `pnpm dlx` instead of `npx` for one-off package execution

## Every project must have

1. `"packageManager": "pnpm@10.30.1"` in `package.json`
2. `pnpm-workspace.yaml` with `minimumReleaseAge: 10080`
3. `pnpm-lock.yaml` (never `package-lock.json` or `yarn.lock`)
